Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.98,0:00:48.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,Sumida River \NKototoi Bridge {隅田川・言問橋}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.24,0:00:53.88,NarTop,,0,0,0,,May 3rd, 1951.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.25,0:00:52.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,May 3rd, 1951
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.88,0:00:55.80,NarTop,,0,0,0,,At Josenji Temple in Mukojima,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.80,0:01:01.08,NarTop,,0,0,0,,The ceremony to elect the second president of Soka Gakkai was held. {向島・常泉寺で創価学会第二代会長の推戴式が挙行された - not exactly inauguration}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.73,0:01:02.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Josenji Temple in Sumida Ward, Tokyo {東京・墨田区の常泉寺}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.78,0:01:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Inaugural address \Nby board chairman Mishima!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.69,0:01:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The emergence of a leader to carry the Buddha Dharma into the future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.17,0:01:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is what we are all longing for in these times.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.45,0:01:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven years have passed \Nsince Soka Gakkai was rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.85,0:01:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,With heartfelt prayers of best wishes from the 3,080 comrades who signed the petition
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.48,0:01:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in support of the president's nomination,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.67,0:01:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I hereby
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.51,0:01:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,nominate Toda Josei-sensei \Nas the second president of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.43,0:01:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know succeeding the late Makiguchi-sensei as the president
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.07,0:02:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is clearly beyond my capacity,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.87,0:02:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is with great faith that I have decided to dedicate my worthless life to Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.75,0:02:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and assume the position \Nof president for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.70,0:02:17.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei will finally \Nbecome the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.51,0:02:20.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,At last, the march forward begins like a scorching sun. {episode title}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.72,0:02:23.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll follow him to the end of the earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,From around the spring of 1943, President Makiguchi began to say
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.48,0:02:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that Soka Gakkai must become the vessel for manifestation of Buddha's true self. {発迹顕本, look notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.56,0:02:33.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,Vessel for manifestation of Buddha's true self
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.23,0:02:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, he would often say, \Nas if reprimanding us,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.07,0:02:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"We must clarify the original mission \Nand purpose of Soka Gakkai and fulfill it."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.06,0:02:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I, his unworthy disciple,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was equally perplexed about how to interpret it, \Nleaving me unable to take any action.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:03:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a profound awareness of its mission has now finally arisen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.18,0:03:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,within the Soka Gakkai as a whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.18,0:03:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Our missionary activities are now more intense than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.31,0:03:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We, Nichiren Daishonin's followers and youngest disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.11,0:03:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,have wholeheartedly accepted the Daishonin's bequest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.03,0:03:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, we will carry on the will of the late Chairman Makiguchi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.54,0:03:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and fulfill our mission to spread the great Buddhist Dharma
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.77,0:03:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Common Path throughout the East and the world. {/the Orient}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.08,0:03:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,May we leave this world with the name \Nof the Great Buddha on our lips. {lit: You must die in the presence of the Great Gohonzon - no idea what he means; 大御本尊の御前において死なんのみであります}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:42.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, the journey to get here
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.83,0:03:46.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was as treacherous as walking along a steep mountain ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.83,0:03:50.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In preparation for the day he would take office,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.62,0:03:55.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda had been quietly working over the past few months to address the issues
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:58.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,facing both the Soka Gakkai and himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.85,0:04:03.86,Sign,,0,0,0,,Shinjuku Ward, Hyakunincho {新宿区百人町}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.46,0:04:04.41,NarTop,,0,0,0,,First, Toda needed to get Daito Trading, \Nwhich he had established
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.86,0:04:06.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,Daito Trading Co., Ltd. {think maybe this last part is unnecessary since "Trading" denotes it as some company clearly enough}{大東商工株式會社}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.41,0:04:06.87,NarTop,,0,0,0,,to rebuild his struggling business,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:10.86,NarTop,,0,0,0,,back on track to secure a financial foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.86,0:04:16.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Daito Trading, a tiny company with four employees, was headed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.47,0:04:22.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,by 23-year-old Yamamoto Shinichi, yet Toda entrusted all the business affairs to them. {lit: entrusted everything to here - probably means he left yamamoto to manage it all himself i.e. laissez-faire}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:28.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although he himself had stepped back from his business to focus on his work for Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:32.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he still visited once a day to offer encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.18,0:04:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.69,0:04:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.84,0:04:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.34,0:04:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't green shoots already sprouting \Nfrom that withered grass?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.34,0:04:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow... What a cute little sprout!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In the eyes of the world, \Nour company may look just like that dead grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.43,0:04:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But when spring comes, \Nnew plants will sprout,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.77,0:05:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and before long, the buds \Nof our business's revival will bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As Nichiren Daishonin wrote in his scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"Those who believe in the Lotus Sutra are like\Nwinter, which never fails to change into spring." {from book}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.80,0:05:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be patient a little longer, \Nso let's hold on to hope and stay strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.39,0:05:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.23,0:05:23.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda began privately tutoring Yamamoto Shinichi, who had to leave his night school
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.36,0:05:24.36,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toda
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:28.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to manage the entire business \Non his behalf behind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.36,0:05:26.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,Eighteen Histories of Ancient China: Brief Summary {十八史略精說}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.13,0:05:32.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Every Sunday, he invited Shinichi to his home
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:35.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and lectured him on a wide range of academic subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.21,0:05:38.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,including politics, economics, and history.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.90,0:05:45.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And Shinichi absorbed it all like water soaking into sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.88,0:05:48.97,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Concerned with promoting the growth and development of Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.97,0:05:53.97,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Toda made enormous efforts to launch the publication of an official bulletin. {/organizational journal}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.02,0:05:59.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,Editorial meeting for the first publication
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:59.73,NarTop,,0,0,0,,He started the first editorial meeting \Nby discussing the paper's future name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.02,0:06:00.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,Culture Magazine {文化新聞}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.73,0:06:00.95,NarTop,,0,0,0,,"Culture Magazine,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.95,0:06:04.59,NarTop,,0,0,0,,"Value Magazine," and other such names were brought up... {/Soka Magazine}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.98,0:06:02.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,Value Magazine {創価新聞}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I just had an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.09,0:06:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's a newspaper that teaches the correct faith, why not "Seikyo Shimbun?" {正しい / tadashi = correct; 正教 / seikyo = orthodox (literally "correct faith") ; check the next few lines before editing}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.24,0:06:11.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Seikyo Shimbun \N(Correct Faith Magazine) {正教新聞}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Seikyo? I see. \NHm... That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.40,0:06:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Seikyo - the Sacred Teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.40,0:06:19.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,Seikyo \N(Sacred Teachings) {聖教}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sei" (Saint) refers to Daishonin's holiness \Nand ascends upwards to Buddha himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A newspaper for the true teachings of Buddha, "Seikyo Shimbun!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.28,0:06:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.28,0:06:31.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Teachings of saints = Seikyo Shimbun {聖の教え = 聖教新聞}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.68,0:06:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Yamamoto-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.14,0:06:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree, it's a wonderful name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.43,0:06:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you wanted to become \Nthe leader of opinions. {lit: male leader in the world of discussion - no clue what he means; 先生が「言論界の雄を目指す」とおっしゃった それにふさわしい名前だと思います}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.36,0:06:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For that purpose, \Nthere isn't a more fitting name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Good. \N"Seikyo Shimbun" it is, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.94,0:06:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.67,0:06:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.94,0:06:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.11,0:06:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is the question of content. First, we need an editorial that will serve as the backbone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.58,0:06:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I would also like a column that criticizes and cuts off the roots of social evil
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.21,0:07:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,from the position of Soka Gakkai. {unsure, sounds really more like "the column that criticizes soka gakkai"; それに 学会批判や社会の悪の根を断ち切るコラムも欲しいね}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.36,0:07:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! \NLet's create a "Short Blade" column, {short blade; small weapon / epigram; pithy saying}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.48,0:07:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with brief but sharp epigrams piercing through minds like a samurai's knife. {そうだ“寸鉄”という囲みを作ろう「寸鉄人を刺す」だ 小さくとも切れ味の鋭いものにしよう}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.16,0:07:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to see some personal accounts in it, \Ndescribing the joy that comes from faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I double that. The social pages of today's newspapers are filled with gloomy news only.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.42,0:07:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, we'll include a lot of personal accounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.11,0:07:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but only as long as our articles are truthful and accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.07,0:07:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If we write without \Nsufficient attention to detail,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.90,0:07:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll just end up being delusional and bigoted like the other sects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fill the rest with a novel. {/works of fiction}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.43,0:07:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? A novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.33,0:07:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, a serialized novel. {actually "full-length "}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.61,0:07:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A newspaper without a serialized novel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.73,0:07:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,won’t have nearly the same appeal \Nas one that includes it. {lit: won't be cool}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.89,0:07:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... But who's going to... \NWill you write it yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. I'll write it. And I'll make sure we don't lose face with my writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.89,0:07:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already decided on a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll call it "human revolution."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.38,0:08:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"Human Revolution..." \NAwesome! I absolutely love that idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take the pen name of "Myogoku" \Nand try to write it to the best of my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.82,0:08:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not sure how long \NI’ll be able to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.08,0:08:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But won't someone be able to take over \Nafter that and keep writing it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.23,0:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,under the name of "Hogoku" or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.03,0:08:30.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,Seikyo Shimbun {right, in the box}\NTakeuchi Keisuke's sentenced to death {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitaka_incident}{竹内景助氏死刑宣告を}\NCommunist party members acquitted {left, smaller font}{共產黨員の信念と妙 - no clue actually}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.79,0:08:33.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And on April 20th, the first issue\Nof Seikyo Shimbun was published.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.06,0:08:32.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,The Human Revolution {人間革命}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.21,0:08:39.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although its circulation was only 5,000, with three issues per month on just two pages,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:44.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda and the Soka Gakkai members were thrilled to hold the new issue in their hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.60,0:08:49.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as they were spearheading the propagation of Common Path and righteous Buddhism. {lit: as they were taking the lead in battle discussions, fighting for the spread of kosen rufu and preaching down; breaking down someone's false beliefs through confrontation (in order to convert them to the right faith)}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.42,0:08:54.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As Toda worked on publishing the newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.20,0:08:58.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,a petition to elect him as president was launched among all Soka Gakkai members,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.33,0:09:01.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,sending everyone into a \Nwhirlwind of excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's nominate Toda-sensei \Nas the president!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.87,0:09:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please read and \Naffix your seals to that petition! {actually "prospectus/letter of intent" but here we clearly see a notebook with a list of signatories so it's probably closer to "the book expressing the majority's opinion"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.25,0:09:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let me see it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.40,0:09:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll sign it! {/put a seal}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.59,0:09:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Write me in too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.77,0:09:24.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,3,080 members who believed in Soka Gakkai and respected Toda Josei signed the petition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.67,0:09:30.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Their representatives are gathered here today \Nwith pride and determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.42,0:09:30.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,Signatures in support of Toda's appointment as a president {戶田会長推戴賛意署名簿 - same on all three}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.99,0:09:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If we wish to attain the same level of enlightenment as the Buddha in this modern age,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.77,0:09:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and sincerely desire the happiness of people and world peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.91,0:09:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we are thorough in our efforts to achieve this,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.50,0:09:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no other way than to spread the Buddhist teaching of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,700 years have passed since \NNichiren Daishonin established the sect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.25,0:10:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As we think about that day approaching next year, when and where in human history
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,has there been a single organization quite like Soka Gakkai in the past 700 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.26,0:10:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as we stand on the doorstep of fulfilling Soka Gakkai's mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.16,0:10:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I can say with my own conviction that I will sacrifice my life for the sake of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.72,0:10:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,During my lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.29,0:10:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I will convert 750,000 households
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.74,0:10:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with my own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:39.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,Huh? 750,000? \NDidn't he mean to say 75,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.24,0:10:41.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,He clearly said 750,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:45.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,But is mass conversion on such a scale even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.27,0:10:49.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,Right now, even with our best efforts, we're only reaching 3,000 households a year at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.44,0:10:51.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda's got big shoes to fill... {/this became serious}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.19,0:10:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I fail to fulfill this sacred wish during my lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask that you do not \Ngive me a proper burial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, just throw my cold body \Ninto the sea off the coast of Shinagawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.31,0:11:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.70,0:11:25.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,We're finally embarking on our active advance towards the Common Path. {/starting to advance towards ... by leaps and bounds}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.56,0:11:29.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei, please lead us into the battle without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.52,0:11:32.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,And I'll have your back at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.98,0:11:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai song - chorus! {unsure how to express this in english - he announces that they'll sing the soka gakkai song as a chorus}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.28,0:11:43.63,Song,,0,0,0,,Like a flower that scatters all its petals overnight {花が一夜に散るごとく\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.63,0:11:49.77,Song,,0,0,0,,I too fly in the wind, like a flag {俺も散りたや旗風に\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:55.78,Song,,0,0,0,,Once I've cast away my body, {どうせ一度は 捨てる身の}{I don't know what they mean anymore}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.78,0:12:01.66,Song,,0,0,0,,Please remember my name fondly, as a man's {名こそ惜しめや男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.09,0:12:14.64,Song,,0,0,0,,Men don't show their tears, but when their hearts come in touch, they do cry {男涙は　見せないが　意気と意気とが　触れて泣く}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:10.02,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,These nameless common people lined up before me now are all Bodhisattvas of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.43,0:12:16.15,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,They truly are an army of Buddhas risking their lives to spread the word of the Lotus Sutra.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.64,0:12:26.98,Song,,0,0,0,,The blood is red in our eyes \Nas we drink to each other's health... {あげる盃　交わす眼に　通うたがいの　血が赤い}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:21.86,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,I wish Makiguchi-sensei could catch a glimpse of this spectacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.46,0:12:25.72,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,How happy would he have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.62,0:12:37.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai President Inauguration Ceremony {創価学会会長就任式}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.03,0:12:37.65,NarTop,,0,0,0,,The birth of the second president \Nwas met with pride and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.65,0:12:40.21,NarTop,,0,0,0,,This launched a self-propelled wave
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.65,0:12:43.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,Kamata branch roundtable discussion {蒲田支部の座談会}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.21,0:12:45.11,NarTop,,0,0,0,,of enthusiasm for disseminating the Common Path among all the Soka Gakkai members.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.11,0:12:50.10,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Roundtable discussions, previously held twice a month, were now springing up all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.10,0:12:52.75,NarTop,,0,0,0,,The newcomers began pouring in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.67,0:12:54.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,Tsurumi branch roundtable discussion {鶴見支部の座談会}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.46,0:12:56.79,NarTop,,0,0,0,,The Buddha Dharma was spreading like wildfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:13:01.21,NarTop,,0,0,0,,The number of monthly conversions, \Nwhich had never exceeded 200 countrywide,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:05.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Koiwa branch roundtable discussion {小岩支部の座談会}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.21,0:13:05.85,NarTop,,0,0,0,,reached the record 284 in May, the month of Toda's inauguration as the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.32,0:13:10.13,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Then several more times with 440 converted households in June
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.14,0:13:14.31,NarTop,,0,0,0,,and the staggering 735 households in July.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.21,0:13:19.81,NarTop,,0,0,0,,During this period, the organization was also actively expanding its presence in the regions,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.84,0:13:23.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,Sendai City, Miyagi Prefecture {宮城県 仙台市}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.81,0:13:21.94,NarTop,,0,0,0,,and immediately after Toda assumed the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.94,0:13:27.95,NarTop,,0,0,0,,the Sendai Branch in Tohoku and the Yame Branch in Kyushu were established.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:27.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,Yame City, Fukuoka Prefecture {福岡県八女市}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:31.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,June 30th \NMonthly branch chiefs meeting {6月30日 月例の支部長会}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.30,0:13:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's change the topic now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.73,0:13:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On the occasion of the 700th anniversary of the Lotus Sutra in April next year,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to publish the complete collection of Nichiren Daishonin's writings!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.42,0:13:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.74,0:13:48.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,With less than a year left \Nuntil next April... It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.68,0:13:53.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,The costs will be through the roof...  \NI wonder if he can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichiren's Scriptures currently in circulation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.72,0:14:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all contain additions or omissions influenced by the publisher's circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.79,0:14:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of these dilute Daishonin's teachings. {/distort}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls to us to follow Daishonin's will to the letter and publish his teachings verbatim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.28,0:14:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To perpetuate the Buddha Dharma,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.69,0:14:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of all future religious revolutions \Nand theological debates,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.33,0:14:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it is imperative
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.28,0:14:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that we print it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I kindly ask for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.81,0:14:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, as for the future of this project,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.81,0:14:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I want it to encompass all of Daishonin's literary remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.83,0:14:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All the publications up to this point \Nwere only partial.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.42,0:14:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, with many misreadings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.25,0:14:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them do not convey \Nthe true intentions of Daishonin-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.47,0:14:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, we will enter an era in which the people will take the initiative in disseminating Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.39,0:14:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A Dharma known only to a handful of people would not be able to keep up with the times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.88,0:15:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's craft a magnificent collection of scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that will endure the test of time, \Nwith our own hands! {lit: that goes forever into the future}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.63,0:15:13.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,Ichigaya Station {市ヶ谷駅}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:23.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's a fresh new beginning today!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.46,0:15:25.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,In just six months, \NI managed to move my office
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.45,0:15:27.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,from barracks to this \Nbrick-and-mortar building!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.50,0:15:34.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,Daito Trading Co., Ltd. {大東商工株式會社}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.28,0:15:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.78,0:15:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.99,0:15:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It finally feels like a proper office.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.31,0:15:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! It's bright and spacious, \Nmakes you feel so very refreshed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.86,0:15:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, we'll be able \Nto work even harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.30,0:15:55.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,Seems like we've taken \Na pretty big step forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.18,0:15:59.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, for Toda-sensei to realize all of his aspirations,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.66,0:16:03.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,we must take the company \Nto the next level.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.68,0:16:12.35,Top,,0,0,0,,I firmly believe that it is we, the youth division—especially the men’s youth division—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:15.01,Top,,0,0,0,,who will forge a path for the unprecedented
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:18.85,Sign,,0,0,0,,July 11th: Men’s Youth Division Formation Ceremony
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.01,0:16:18.83,Top,,0,0,0,,religious revolution that the Common Path will usher in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:21.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A historic formation ceremony for the Men's Youth Division
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.85,0:16:26.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,brought together 180 young men, signaling a new era for the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:30.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi also participated as a subdivision leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.88,0:16:33.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,No one could have foreseen that this
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.53,0:16:38.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,seemingly small gathering would eventually flow into a mighty river,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.48,0:16:41.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,uniting millions of young men \Nin a single endeavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.92,0:16:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm confident that the next president of Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,will rise from among the young men gathered here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.86,0:16:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It is my sincere conviction \Nthat is already among you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.37,0:16:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.87,0:17:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to extend my heartfelt congratulations to that person, whoever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:06.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,That day half a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.13,0:17:10.96,Sign,,0,0,0,,January 6th
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.10,0:17:10.93,Top,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, I need you to give me a serious answer to something today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.32,0:17:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.93,0:17:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important now is what comes after...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.86,0:17:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If something were to happen to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.05,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to leave the Soka Gakkai, the credit cooperative, and the Daito Trading in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you accept it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, if only doable, \Nmy family too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.16,0:17:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.46,0:17:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi-kun, my mission in this world is also your mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.69,0:17:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you and I live our mission together,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the time will surely come when Daishonin's legacy is fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.47,0:18:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what anyone says, let's stay strong and move forward together!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.10,0:18:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, you have nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided long ago that if I dedicate my entire life to you, I’ll have no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.59,0:18:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And my resolve won’t waver, \Nno matter how many years pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.41,0:18:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That's all I could wish for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.86,0:18:32.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei is in much better spirits now \Nthan he was back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.83,0:18:34.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,Nothing brings me greater happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.85,0:18:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It is my solemn desire that you will fulfill this noble and formidable mission
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.17,0:18:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of achieving Common Path \Nwith your own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.12,0:18:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I want to greet my future successor, the next president of Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.33,0:18:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and offer my heartfelt congratulations \Non the formation of the Men's Youth Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.49,0:19:01.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Next, Women's Youth Division formation ceremony was held.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.79,0:19:06.27,Top,,0,0,0,,I like to believe that every member of our Women's Youth Division has found happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.27,0:19:11.85,Top,,0,0,0,,In the past, women often could do nothing but cry because of their unfortunate fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.85,0:19:16.29,Top,,0,0,0,,You are all fortunate women who embraced the Mystic Law at a young age
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.29,0:19:19.34,Top,,0,0,0,,and no longer have to weep over your fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.82,0:19:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.56,0:19:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sincerely dedicating yourself to faith in your youth
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.70,0:19:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,will pave the way for a happy life \Nand a future family.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.10,0:19:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It is my heartfelt wish that each and every one of you finds happiness as I speak to you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.16,0:19:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.27,0:19:52.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although fighting continued on the Korean peninsula, armistice talks finally began in July.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:56.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was anticipated that the war \Nwould soon subside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.57,0:20:04.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Korean people don't deserve to suffer any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.66,0:20:07.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,I want this war to end as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:16.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's also evident that the Allied occupation of Japan will soon come to an end. {actually "the peace treaty will soon be concluded" but he actually refers to the transition from postwar to independence as a whole}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.06,0:20:21.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,Many people long for a lasting peace with all the Allied powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.59,0:20:25.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,And yet, the belligerent countries keep exchanging fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.64,0:20:30.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,What's worse is that a treaty that ignores the interests of neighboring Soviet Union and China
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.64,0:20:32.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,is ultimately meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.72,0:20:37.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,Especially China, to whom we've caused so much suffering... {hope he means this; 特に中国には多大な迷惑をかけているだけに････}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.51,0:20:45.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,In the end, even after we regain our independence, {/peace treaty is signed}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.06,0:20:49.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,the Japanese nation will essentially remain the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.83,0:20:56.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Treaty of Peace with Japan, marking the end of the war
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.00,0:20:57.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the restoration of Japan’s sovereignty,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.58,0:21:00.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,The historic peace is signed {歷史的講和會議調印終る}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.88,0:21:05.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was signed in San Francisco on September 8th by 49 countries, excluding the communist bloc.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.38,0:21:00.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,{same}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.58,0:21:06.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,Special issue: San Francisco Peace Treaty is signed {above; サンフランシスコ講和条約・今曉調印}\N49 countries participate; Japanese flag is raised {right vertical; 四十九ヵ国が参加 晴れて日章旗ける}\NYoshida Shigeru's speech {below; 吉田全權演說}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.59,0:21:10.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Japan reestablished itself as an independent nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:15.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It seemed as though the era of occupation, symbolized by GHQ,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.40,0:21:17.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was finally drawing to a close.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.57,0:21:23.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister Yoshida signs the Security Treaty {安保条約に調印する吉田全権}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.22,0:21:23.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, alongside the peace treaty, \Nthe Japan-US Security Treaty was signed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.93,0:21:25.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,permitting the US military
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.32,0:21:31.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to continue using bases in Japan and remain stationed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.37,0:21:35.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,May Day protests going awry {above; メーデーの流れ暴動化す}\NPublic order disturbance investigation {left;「騷擾罪」で徹底捜査}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.84,0:21:35.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But the security treaty \Nwas met with fierce opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.37,0:21:37.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,First May Day since independence: 400,000 people gather at Gaien Square {right vertical; 独立後初のメーデー\N外苑広場に四十 万}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.83,0:21:40.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Civil unrest over the security treaty \Nwill persist long after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.42,0:21:45.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Despite the signing of the peace treaty with Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.63,0:21:47.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,just as Toda had predicted,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.57,0:21:52.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the reality was that Japan remained essentially unchanged,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.63,0:21:56.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,still far from being truly independent or democratic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.60,0:22:03.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,It all stems from the lack of a firm idea about the right ideology in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:09.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,The only solution is the Common Path. \NAnd for that we require a lot more men,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.21,0:22:11.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,aware that their mission is the Common Path
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.45,0:22:15.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,and determined to carry the future of Japan on their shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.31,0:22:22.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's the youth! We must cultivate young men into the leaders of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.62,0:22:30.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda began composing a piece titled "Message to Group Leaders"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.62,0:22:34.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to clarify guidelines, and offer hope and encouragement
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.65,0:22:39.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to the young people representing the future of the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.65,0:22:39.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,"Message to Group Leaders" {班長に告ぐ}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.66,0:22:48.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll try to put into words the noble goal of Soka Gakkai, its spirit, and everything in my heart. {unsure: 崇高な学会の目的 精神 そして私の心の中にあるものをすべてぶつけてみよう}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.49,0:22:54.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,I have to ensure that it lives on unchanged forever in the hearts of young men.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.20,0:22:58.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes. Let's start with the conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.30,0:23:07.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,"It is the passion and energy of the youth \Nthat will form a new century."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.71,0:23:15.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,It is the passion and energy of the youth that will form a new century.\NWe can't discuss politics or intuit education, but we follow the great world philosopher, savior of the East, and the True Embodiment of Buddha who appeared in Japan in the Latter Day of the Law. {check notes}{新しき世紀を創るものは、青年の熱と力である。\N吾人らは、政治を論じ、教育を勘がうる者ではないが、世界大哲・東洋の救世主・日本出世の末法御本仏たる}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.09,0:23:11.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As soon as this "Message to Group Leaders" was released,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.08,0:23:18.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it swept through the Youth Division like a gust of wind, sending shockwaves across its ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.51,0:23:23.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,A notice is issued to the youth division leader {right, bold; 青年部班長へ告示下る}\NThe president of Soka Gakkai calls on all male and female members {left, smaller; 創價學會會長先生より男女青年部員奮起せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.82,0:23:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"Rise up, young people! \NWe've got a fight ahead of us, young people. {actually funki is more like "rouse yourself" so idk what to put here}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.13,0:23:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You may ask, then, who are we fighting \Nand what is our strategy?" {no idea: しからば 誰人と如何なる戦を吾人等はなすものであろうか}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.04,0:23:40.71,Top,,0,0,0,,"Thirdly, it is a battle in which we must love all living beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.71,0:23:47.67,Top,,0,0,0,,That said, a lot of young people don't even love their own parents, so how can they love others?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.57,0:23:56.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,Shinichi Yamamoto's apartment in Omori, Ota Ward {大田区 大森・山本伸一のアパート}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.67,0:23:52.78,Top,,0,0,0,,The answer is by overcoming one's callousness and attaining the Buddha's compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.78,0:23:55.55,Top,,0,0,0,,in the battle of human revolution!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.54,0:24:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"You must unite your hearts and, \Nas the young flowering warriors you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,overcome your difficulties with a sincere desire to honor Daishonin’s legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.61,0:24:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Recognition from fools is the ignominy of the wise. {lit: being praised by fools is a shame of the wise person - wise person can also be "Bodhisattva/buddhist priest", also unsure why ほむらるる is spelled this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.72,0:24:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Recognition from Daishonin \Nis a lifetime honor."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.87,0:24:22.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,What stern yet warm words... \NThis message is brimming with sensei's emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.28,0:24:27.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it's the lion's cry \Nfor the salvation of humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.07,0:24:32.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This "Message to Group Leaders" would later become "Instruction to Youth,"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.88,0:24:37.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,igniting many young men with burning enthusiasm
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.81,0:24:42.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and inspiration to lead the fight for the Common Path on the front lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.59,0:24:49.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Around that time, Soka Gakkai was gaining more and more recognition in society
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.60,0:24:53.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as an independent religious movement with its own distinct activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.54,0:24:57.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that any future expansion
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.45,0:25:00.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of Common Path activities would need to be multifaceted,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.75,0:25:03.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda began preparing to register Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.04,0:25:07.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as a religious organization \Nunder the Religious Corporations Ordinance. {no official english translation, but this refers to it this way: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Religious_Organizations_Law#}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.31,0:25:13.84,NarTop,,0,0,0,,What is the purpose and reasoning behind Soka Gakkai's decision to separate from the sect
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.84,0:25:17.19,NarTop,,0,0,0,,and become an independent religious organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.19,0:25:19.62,NarTop,,0,0,0,,First and foremost, it was to allow them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.15,0:25:22.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,"Preaching Guidebook" published on November 18th {11月18日発刊された「折伏教典」}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.62,0:25:23.87,NarTop,,0,0,0,,the freedom to independently pursue various activities aimed at spreading the Common Path,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.15,0:25:28.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Opinion magazine "The Third Civilization" {言論誌「第三文明」}{/daisanbunmeisha}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.87,0:25:27.52,NarTop,,0,0,0,,including propagation efforts, publishing, and public debates.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.52,0:25:32.99,NarTop,,0,0,0,,And by extension, to engage in efforts that contribute to the improvement and development
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.15,0:25:35.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Educational theory magazine "The Lighthouse" {/The Todai}{教育理論誌「灯台」}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.99,0:25:37.11,NarTop,,0,0,0,,of peace, culture, and education in line with Soka Gakkai's unique path.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.15,0:25:44.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,The first athletic meeting/youth festival of the Youth Division, which became the origin of today's cultural festivals {今日の文化祭の淵源となる青年部初の体育大会/若人の祭典}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.80,0:25:43.53,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Secondly, it was to help Soka Gakkai withstand any hardships that might arise while preaching
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.53,0:25:45.81,NarTop,,0,0,0,,and spreading Nichiren's teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.68,0:25:53.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,4th East Japan Athletic Meeting\NPresident Toda's "Declaration Calling for the Abolition of Nuclear Weapons"\N(September 8, 1957, Mitsuzawa Stadium, Yokohama) {第4回 東日本体育大会\N戸田会長による「原水爆禁止宣言」\N(昭和32年9月8日 横浜・三ツ沢競技場)}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.81,0:25:50.21,NarTop,,0,0,0,,This allowed them to carry out their duties of saving the laity without creating
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.21,0:25:53.18,NarTop,,0,0,0,,any responsibilities or inconveniences for the sect overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.18,0:25:57.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thirdly, in the current complex social structure
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.41,0:26:02.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and in anticipation of the future global spread of the Common Path teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.02,0:26:05.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to countries with diverse cultures and lifestyles,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.75,0:26:11.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,relying on a small number of priests—who already manage their own congregations—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.11,0:26:15.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,for that goal was, at best, unrealistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.22,0:26:19.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Fourthly, it was natural for a religious organization
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.36,0:26:23.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to center around the people and decide its activities
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.24,0:26:29.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,by consensus, reflecting the people's sentiments in light of current democratic trends.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.19,0:26:34.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Finally, in August of the following year, 1952,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.37,0:26:39.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai was officially recognized as a religious organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.71,0:26:43.16,NarTop,,0,0,0,,As a religious organization under the Religious Corporations Ordinance,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.16,0:26:49.22,NarTop,,0,0,0,,it gained the legal foundation to conduct activities independently from the sect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.21,0:26:49.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,Tokyo Kasei-Gakuin University, Ichigaya {市ヶ谷・東京家政学院}{/Tokyo home economy university}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.21,0:26:55.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,November 4th: 6th Soka Gakkai General Meeting {11月4日 第6回創価学会総会}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.09,0:26:55.22,Top,,0,0,0,,Determinations and aspirations \Nof each division's representative!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.22,0:27:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The title is “Youth's Conviction” by Men's Division Representative, Group Leader Yamamoto. Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.22,0:27:01.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,Youth's Conviction \NGroup Leader Yamamoto {青年の山本班長確信}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.24,0:27:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai President Toda Josei!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.14,0:27:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The youth of Soka Gakkai are now engaged in a great struggle
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.66,0:27:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,towards a clear goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.64,0:27:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as outlined in the recent "Message to the Youth of Soka Gakkai" from Toda-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.24,0:27:22.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The speech of Men's Division Group Leader Yamamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.57,0:27:28.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,filled with determination and aspirations, was a direct response to Toda Josei's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.02,0:27:31.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Message to the Group Leaders," published a month earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.65,0:27:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Toda-sensei is issuing a great decree as the general of the Common Path
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.98,0:27:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Latter Day of the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.14,0:27:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We, the Youth Division, \Nhave taken his words to heart
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.31,0:27:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and are ready to devote our souls and bodies to spreading the Great Law with a smile! {我ら青年部は先生のお心を心として この身を大法流布のために莞爾として散らしかんじ}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.77,0:27:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Spending our lives with Toda-sensei's teachings is our sacred wish! {actually "live with sensei forever" so idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.04,0:27:58.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is the first time I’ve heard Shinichi speak to such a large audience, and he's quite good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.44,0:28:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The task that lies before the youth division is a religious revolution!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.95,0:28:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The path to a religious revolution will be far more challenging
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.30,0:28:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,than that of any political or economic one, \Nand we must be prepared for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.07,0:28:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,President Toda Josei!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.34,0:28:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The youth of Soka Gakkai have triumphed over every obstacle
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.11,0:28:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and now stand in the world's spotlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.16,0:28:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, we are confident that we will see our struggle through to the end
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.35,0:28:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and fulfill the expectations of Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.71,0:28:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,President’s Lecture \N"The Great Pledge of Soka Gakkai!"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.24,0:28:52.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just as Yamamoto Shinichi's announcement of his determination, "The Conviction of Youth,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.70,0:28:55.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was a pledge of loyalty to Toda Josei,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.88,0:29:03.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda's speech "The Great Vow of the Soka Gakkai," was his pledge of loyalty to the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.96,0:29:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I vow to spread the true teachings of Buddha Dharma across this nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.56,0:29:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,where so many are afflicted \Nby their erroneous faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.79,0:29:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is article 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.43,0:29:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As a follower of the Buddha Dharma, I will spread Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.78,0:29:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from Japan to Korea, China, and India, thereby fulfilling Daishonin's prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.44,0:29:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Such is my vow to the Common Path. \NAnd our second goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.21,0:29:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.98,0:29:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we devote our bodies and souls to the spread of Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.56,0:29:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as our measly offering \Nto the Great Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.01,0:29:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us show the religious world that Soka Gakkai is here to stay!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.04,0:29:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This and the two other articles \Nare my immediate goals,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.60,0:29:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that reflect the unanimous wish \Nof all Soka Gakkai members.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.50,0:29:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you with me, friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.88,0:30:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.52,0:30:06.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,Daito Trading Co., Ltd. {大東商工株式會社}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.49,0:30:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, I see we're finally back on track.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.49,0:30:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. At this rate, we might be able to pay off our credit union debts sooner than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.35,0:30:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. You did a great job
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.15,0:30:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mention it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.41,0:30:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll work even harder to allow you more freedom and control in leading the Common Path forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.72,0:30:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.91,0:30:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yessir!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.22,0:30:41.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,It seems that all the hard work Shin put in \Nhas helped him grow a lot stronger...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.92,0:30:47.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hmm, our preaching progress has been quite stagnant lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.49,0:30:50.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,neither increasing nor decreasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.19,0:30:52.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,Our conversion goal of 1,000 households
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.31,0:30:55.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,per month by October doesn't seem achievable anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.35,0:30:58.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,At this rate, the promised 750,000 households...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.64,0:30:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.77,0:31:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a couple of places to visit now to discuss a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.02,0:31:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, go ahead. \NYou're doing very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.03,0:31:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be on my way, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.08,0:31:17.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hm... Is it time to put Shin \Non the front lines?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.98,0:31:20.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,Shin is already my right-hand man.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.40,0:31:27.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,He might just be able to devise the breakthrough we need to overcome this stagnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.20,0:31:34.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei announced that we are intensifying our preaching efforts. {lit: declared big preaching down - unsure what he means, maybe "his intentions to go global"}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.88,0:31:39.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei is the master of preaching, \Nand I am his disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.02,0:31:44.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Converting 750,000 households \Nis my goal as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.22,0:31:51.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,I cannot let Toda-sensei down \Nand allow him to break his oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.69,0:31:56.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The battle in which Toda Josei \Nand Yamamoto Shinichi
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.41,0:32:02.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,are engaged in an unprecedented effort to spread the Lotus Sutra to 750,000 families
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.12,0:32:07.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and create a society filled with happiness and peace
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.34,0:32:13.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,is finally unfolding, stirring up stormy winds and dark clouds along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.33,0:33:16.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,
